,Recommended,429720,30696570,Posted: 23 March,all,Malkavian,"Disclaimer:There's two ways to approach the decision of whether or not to buy this game, and I'll explain why right after. You can download and play the free version ofIMSCAREDwhere you will only be able to play Chapter 1. If you like it enough to want to play the actual complete version of the game, buy it here. The only downside is that youwillhave to replay Chapter 1 once you purchase it. Otherwise, stop reading about this game now, buy it, and take it from there. The reason I say this is becauseIMSCAREDis an indie metahorror game that plays like a blurry fever dream. It's a niche addition to an already obscure and underplayed sub-genre of horror adventure games that might mess with people's standards of what to expect from an adventure horror game.IMSCAREDis a metahorror fever dream that has you as the protagonist. It creates a desktop folder where it will upload .txt, .htm .config files that you will have to read and alter in order to progress throught the game. It's an incredibly ingenious game that will have you oscillating between the game, the desktop folder and whatever linksithas you follow. If you stick around the end credits you will see one of the creators decided you claim anonimity through the witty pseudonym of ""you see? you can do so much with so little"" (or something like that). I think that's cute and funny. But most importantly, purposefully or not, I think that illustrates the core philosophy ofIMSCARED. The sound was created using FL Studio 10, the game itself was made with the help of GameJolt and the graphis are pixelated! Yet, this game manages to produce crips and jarring sound effects that, if played with the volume on mid/high, will undoubtedly scare you. Despite utilizing the one of the 'lowest' forms of visual illustration, it manages to craft cozy and interesting levels filled with inexplicable nostalgia and mystery.Furthermore, whereIMSCAREDshines is through its script. The .txt files the game creates in your desktop folder comprise an apocalyptic log that compliments the eerie sense of being watched byWhite Facethroughout the whole game.#Discussions_QuoteBlock_AuthorThere is a way to turn an entity into data. They have a life of their own, and it is difficult to disntinguish them from normal computer files. In our actions of everyday, while we sit at the computer, this byte entity observes us, and studies our every move and fear.This is one of the first messagesIMSCAREDcreates in your computer and it is oddly profound for a pixelated game. A philosophical question at heart, admittedly fiction at the moment, but engaging to ponder. That is the main premise of the game --consciousness transferred into data-- and it executes it fairly effective for its medium.IMSCAREDdecidedly establishes it's place amongst other similar games, such asUndertale,Pony IslandandEternal Darkness; and that, although not entirely horror, effectively break the 4th wall and interact directly with the player.If you enjoy the way I review games, join and follow my curator group! It comes with a fun discord channel for horror fans to chill and game.Malkavian Madness"
