,Recommended,429720,24072225,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,Yaridovich,"9/10This game is an incredibly good horror game that has a good combination of creepy atmosphere and jump scares. It actually reminded me a lot of a different horror game I've played called I See You. It's the kind of game that makes you think you're playing the role of a character, but the game actually makes it feel like it's trying to interact directly with you, the player behind the screen.And it's exactly for that reason that the game manages to be so disturbing. I won't spoil the actual mechanics the game uses to interact with the player, but I can say it'll catch a lot of people by surprise - and often. It constantly tricks the player into thinking he/she has accomplished something or that they've finished the game, only to then reveal something new.The only flaw I've found in the game is movement. While the actual controls work as intended, it's easy to get stuck at walls, which can be a problem when you're trying to run from something. Also, for some reason, you can't strafe when crouching. It's not actually a problem, but it feels weird.Overall, if I had to compile a list of must-play horror games, IMSCARED would definitely be included."
