,Recommended,429720,22307117,"Posted: 8 April, 2016",all,Wand3r3r3,"So I'm just going to review this now before I get fed up with the easy accidental, quitting game thing where ESC is to pause, and clicking is to resume. I have a bad habit of ESCing all the time. But NOT because I'm spooked x3Well, that's actually a pretty plausible reason; if I was spooked pretty badly. But I can't get spooked badly, because I keep accidentally quittiiiiiing D:But ANYWAY, with a super short, super simple, super indie game like IMSCARED, don't be fooled—it's in caps for a reason. And these are the kinds of games that get me the most, and I love them. This updated version of the game that was originally found elsewhere gives you an easy—and brief—tutorial on how to play. I'm not kidding, it really is a simple game with kb/m controls. WSAD movements, ctrl kneeling, E to interact, and shift to sprint. Nothing more.It's hard to believe that none of my friends here own this $4 game. It's absolutely wonderful. Easily paralyzing, too. It basically makes a folder in your computer's Documents to attack you many many many times throughout the game.This game is a real experience."
