,Recommended,429720,21262590,"Posted: 16 February, 2016",all,CHOOD,"What an incredible and truly unique experience. The atmosphere is menacing, the scares are terrifying, the music is creepy and fitting, and the ending is unforgettable.The antagonist messes with your head psychologically, then emotionally. You will feel very uncomfortable as you are forced to make heartless and horrible decisions, but this leads to one of the most bittersweet moments in gaming I have ever experienced.Some of the puzzles were very clever and fun, forcing you to think outside of the box in order to solve them in ways no other game has thought of. However, they aren't perfect. A couple puzzles were very tedious: the hedgemaze and the grammophone puzzles specifically. Without spoiling anything, these were a pain to get through and were the only sections that are actually detrimental to full experience.The game could use some more graphics options. Forcing the player to play in a lower resolution is archaic and creates a delay when having to alt+tab to the folder. There are also no FOV options or checkbox to turn off headbob. These two options would prevent a lot of simulation sickness for those that can get a little light-headed from first person view video games.That all being said, any fan of horror should definitely check this out. It is beatable in 2-3 hours, and fully worth the price of $4."
