,Recommended,429720,22561040,"Posted: 21 April, 2016",all,Turnoverman,"I'm not the sort that likes horror games. I don't have anything against them, they're just not my thing. I prefer either power-fantasy type deals (like Dynasty Warriors) or stuff that appeals to planning (like XCOM or Wasteland 2). I do particularly like the ever-rare metagame, though. The sort wot is like Hack n' Slash or The Magic Circle.As that particular type of game is super rare, when I found out that this game is also that, I jumped on it.As per usual with metagames, the less said about it the better.As for the horror bits from someone who *really* doesn't care about horror (and as such is woefully unqualified to tell anyone if horror is good or not), it was pretty good. At least a few of the jumpscares actually got me and the general mood of it is fairly spoopy. That wasn't my core engagement, though. I just wanted to know the next way the game would screw with me.Take this as a recommendation purely for the metagame. It makes sitting through the horror-y bits worth it even if you're completely ambivalent towards them. I can't imagine that it'll outweigh a particular dislike for horror, though."
